            "title": "Europe must prepare for 'long-lasting' energy shock, EU energy commissioner tells FT",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>April 3 (Reuters) - The European Union is assessing \"all possibilities\" including fuel rationing and releasing more oil from emergency reserves as it braces for a \"long-lasting\" energy shock from the Middle East war, the Financial Times reported on Friday in an interview with European Union energy commissioner Dan Jorgensen.</p><p>\n\n\"This will be a long crisis ... energy prices will be higher for a very long time,\" Dan Jorgensen told the Financial Times, saying that for some more \"critical\" products \"we expect it to be even worse in the weeks to come\".</p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n(Reporting by Disha Mishra in Bengaluru; Editing by Christopher Cushing)</p></div>",
